    {
      "id": "data_sources",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Multi-Source Market Inputs\n\nReal-time:\n- Angel One ticks\n- OHLCV candles\n- options chain and IV surface\n- futures chain\n- spread/volume/open interest when available\n\nContext:\n- NSE/BSE/MCX sessions\n- corporate actions\n- economic calendar\n- news and social sentiment\n- broker orders/fills\n- portfolio and margin state",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 360,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "streaming_bus",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Streaming Backbone\n\nLocal phase:\n- existing `InMemoryEventBus`\n- SQLite durable mirrors\n- asyncio queues\n\nScale phase:\n- Redpanda/Kafka or NATS JetStream\n- idempotent consumers\n- topic-per-event-domain\n\nTopics:\n`tick.raw`, `bar.closed`, `option.chain`, `features`, `agent.vote`, `model.prediction`, `quantum.result`, `risk.veto`, `order.event`.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": -230,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 370,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "lakehouse",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Research Lakehouse\n\nReplayable data store:\n- raw ticks and bars\n- cleaned candles\n- option snapshots\n- model features\n- LLM agent summaries\n- optimizer requests/results\n- OMS and fills\n- realized slippage and PnL\n\nSuggested production stack:\nClickHouse or TimescaleDB for time series, Parquet for history, SQLite for local bootstrap.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 200,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 340,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "feature_store",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Feature Store\n\nFeature families:\n- micro price/volume features\n- momentum and trend strength\n- volatility and realized variance\n- options Greeks and IV surface\n- liquidity and impact estimates\n- regime features\n- macro/news embeddings\n- portfolio exposure features\n\nEvery vector is versioned with source data id and timestamp.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 600,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "vector_memory",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Vector Memory and RAG\n\nUsed by local Gemma agents for grounded reasoning:\n- strategy docs\n- broker API docs\n- past trade postmortems\n- market news archives\n- model cards and experiments\n- compliance notes\n\nAgent outputs must cite retrieved evidence ids.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 990,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "label_factory",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Label and Outcome Factory\n\nLabels:\n- triple-barrier outcome\n- forward return buckets\n- drawdown after entry\n- volatility expansion\n- stop/target hit order\n- slippage surprise\n- news reaction\n\nUsed by neural models, quantum kernel experiments, and meta-labeling.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 1330,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 290,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "realtime_state",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Real-Time State Store\n\nLow-latency state:\n- current marks\n- open positions\n- portfolio exposures\n- active exit plans\n- kill switch\n- model health\n- agent votes\n- active policy version\n\nBacked by existing runtime locally; Redis later.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 1680,
      "width": 1400,
      "height": 270,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_control_tower",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Agent Control Tower\n\nDeterministic orchestrator coordinates specialist agents.\n\nPatterns:\n- manager agent for research synthesis\n- code-owned orchestration for trading decisions\n- parallel agents for independent market views\n- debate for strategy review\n- hard timeouts and token budgets\n\nOnly structured outputs enter the trade path.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 1680,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "gemma_gateway",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Local Gemma-Compatible Model Gateway\n\nPhase 2 target: add model gateway, not custom model creation.\n\nLocal runtimes:\n- vLLM for GPU serving\n- Ollama or llama.cpp for workstation serving\n- deterministic stubs for tests\n\nModel routing:\n- `gemma4-31b`: chief analyst/reasoner\n- `gemma4-26b-moe`: desk coordinator\n- `gemma4-e4b/e2b`: fast micro-agents\n\nControls:\n- structured JSON output\n- RAG retrieval\n- tool schema awareness\n- no broker credentials\n- no direct order tools",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": -260,
      "width": 1680,
      "height": 390,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_news",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## News and Macro Agent\n\nReads news/calendar/social embeddings.\n\nOutputs:\n- event risk score\n- affected symbols/sectors\n- likely volatility window\n- source confidence\n- reason summary\n\nCan recommend HALT or REDUCE, never increase risk alone.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": 190,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 290,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_quant",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quant Research Agent\n\nAnalyzes:\n- feature importance\n- strategy decay\n- alpha hypotheses\n- model diagnostics\n- failed trade clusters\n\nOutputs research tickets, ablation requests, and drift warnings. Runs outside live order path.",
      "x": -1500,
      "y": 190,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 290,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_strategy_council",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Strategy Council Agents\n\nSpecialists:\n- trend/momentum\n- mean reversion\n- breakout\n- gap/event\n- pairs/stat-arb\n- options volatility\n- futures carry/basis\n- hedge builder\n\nEach returns `StrategyProposal` with edge, risk, evidence, and invalidation rule.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": 540,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 350,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_risk_critic",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Risk Critic Agent\n\nTries to kill weak trades before risk engine.\n\nChecks:\n- stale data\n- crowding\n- correlated exposure\n- event risk\n- high slippage\n- model disagreement\n- goal-pressure overtrading\n\nOutput is advisory reduction or veto recommendation.",
      "x": -1500,
      "y": 540,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 350,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_portfolio_pm",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Portfolio Manager Agent\n\nCombines strategy proposals with capital state.\n\nOutputs:\n- preferred basket\n- expected return distribution\n- allocation request\n- hedge request\n- max allowed heat\n- target run-rate comparison\n\nFeeds quantum and classical optimizers.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": 950,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_execution",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Execution Analyst Agent\n\nAnalyzes fill quality and market impact.\n\nInputs:\n- recent fills\n- spread and volume\n- rejected orders\n- broker latency\n\nOutputs order slicing or avoid-window advice. ExecutionScheduler still owns routing.",
      "x": -1500,
      "y": 950,
      "width": 800,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_debate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Agent Debate and Vote Board\n\nHigh-conviction trades require:\n1. bull case\n2. bear case\n3. risk critic\n4. portfolio manager\n5. supervisor adjudicator\n\nLow consensus or high uncertainty means no trade.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": 1330,
      "width": 1680,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_trace",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Agent Trace Contract\n\nEvery agent output includes:\n- trace id\n- local model id\n- input data ids\n- retrieved evidence ids\n- schema version\n- confidence\n- failure mode\n- recommended action\n\nUnstructured text is UI explanation only.",
      "x": -2340,
      "y": 1670,
      "width": 1680,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "neural_feature_factory",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Neural Feature Factory\n\nTransforms market/event data into tensors:\n- multi-timeframe candles\n- indicators and realized vol\n- options surface tensors\n- sector graph features\n- news embeddings\n- portfolio state\n\nOutputs normalized model-ready batches.",
      "x": -290,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "forecast_ensemble",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Forecasting Ensemble\n\nModels:\n- Temporal Fusion Transformer\n- PatchTST / time-series transformer\n- N-BEATS / N-HiTS\n- LSTM/GRU baseline\n- tree/linear baseline\n\nPredictions:\n- return quantiles\n- direction probability\n- volatility bands\n- stop/target hit probability\n\nUse calibration before trading.",
      "x": 500,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 360,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "gnn_model",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Cross-Asset Graph Model\n\nGraph nodes:\n- stocks\n- indices\n- sectors\n- futures\n- option underlyings\n\nEdges:\n- rolling correlation\n- sector membership\n- lead-lag effects\n- shared macro sensitivity\n\nOutputs contagion and correlation risk.",
      "x": -290,
      "y": -270,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "vol_tail_model",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Volatility and Tail-Risk Models\n\nModels:\n- GARCH baseline\n- deep volatility forecaster\n- quantile regression network\n- extreme move classifier\n- drawdown predictor\n\nOutputs feed sizing, hedging, and event risk gates.",
      "x": 500,
      "y": -230,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 290,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "sentiment_model",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Sentiment and Event Model\n\nPipeline:\n- news ingestion\n- LLM event extraction\n- embedding classifier\n- symbol/sector linker\n- sentiment decay model\n\nOutput joins numerical features as explainable event factor.",
      "x": -290,
      "y": 120,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "marl_lab",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Multi-Agent RL Lab\n\nUse Ray RLlib / FinRL-style simulation.\n\nAgents:\n- entry policy\n- exit policy\n- hedge policy\n- sizing policy\n- execution policy\n- adversarial slippage agent\n\nOffline/simulated only until shadow and paper promotion.",
      "x": 500,
      "y": 140,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "meta_labeler",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Meta-Labeling and Champion/Challenger\n\nCombines:\n- rule strategies\n- neural predictions\n- agent votes\n- quantum suggestions\n- realized outcomes\n\nPromotes strategies by regime only after out-of-sample baseline improvement.",
      "x": -290,
      "y": 470,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "model_serving",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Low-Latency Model Serving\n\nLocal phase:\n- in-process Python models\n- ONNX for critical neural models\n\nScale phase:\n- Ray Serve / Triton / vLLM\n- GPU batch inference\n- version pinning\n- warm standby fallback\n\nNever blocks exit manager or kill switch.",
      "x": 500,
      "y": 530,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 310,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "neural_output",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Neural Prediction Bundle\n\nTyped output:\n- expected return distribution\n- direction probability\n- volatility forecast\n- tail-risk score\n- liquidity risk\n- correlation risk\n- model uncertainty\n- calibrated confidence\n- model version ids\n\nInput to decision blackboard and optimizer.",
      "x": -290,
      "y": 890,
      "width": 1530,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_orchestrator",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum Orchestrator\n\nRuns only after data quality passes.\n\nJobs:\n- portfolio selection\n- constrained basket optimization\n- dynamic rebalancing research\n- quantum kernel experiments\n- quantum-inspired baseline benchmark\n\nNever trades directly. Returns proposals with baseline comparison.",
      "x": 1560,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 1530,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_feature_map",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum Data Encoding\n\nConvert normalized market features into quantum-compatible feature maps.\n\nUse small feature sets:\n- regime features\n- volatility features\n- return/risk embeddings\n- option surface summary\n\nResearch/shadow first.",
      "x": 1560,
      "y": -290,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 310,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_kernel",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum Kernel Classifier\n\nResearch use:\n- regime classification\n- anomaly detection\n- high-volatility state separation\n\nUses quantum kernel matrix with classical classifiers.\n\nShadow only until walk-forward improvement is proven.",
      "x": 2360,
      "y": -290,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 310,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "qubo_optimizer",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## QUBO/CQM Portfolio Optimizer\n\nInputs:\n- candidate basket\n- expected edge vector\n- covariance/risk matrix\n- transaction costs\n- margin and lot approximations\n- liquidity constraints\n- target run-rate pressure\n\nObjective: maximize risk-adjusted expected return while respecting budget, drawdown, concentration, and liquidity.",
      "x": 1560,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 360,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "qiskit_backend",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## IBM/Qiskit Backend\n\nResearch methods:\n- VQE for QUBO portfolio optimization\n- QAOA-style combinatorial optimization\n- Qiskit Function portfolio optimizer where available\n\nUse for pre-market, EOD, or research. Not millisecond execution.",
      "x": 2360,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "dwave_backend",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## D-Wave Hybrid Backend\n\nBest fit:\n- constrained candidate selection\n- portfolio subset selection\n- hedge basket selection\n- rebalancing with cardinality and budget constraints\n\nUses CQM/BQM/DQM/nonlinear hybrid solvers when configured. Disabled by default.",
      "x": 1560,
      "y": 500,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_inspired",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum-Inspired Classical Baseline\n\nAlways run first:\n- exact enumeration for small baskets\n- greedy local search\n- simulated annealing\n- genetic/local search\n- scipy/cvxpy where suitable\n\nQuantum result must beat or diversify this baseline before influencing paper trades.",
      "x": 2360,
      "y": 480,
      "width": 720,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_gate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum Result Gate\n\nAccept quantum proposal only if:\n- completed within timeout\n- constraints satisfied\n- objective >= classical threshold\n- stable across perturbation samples\n- basket passes risk precheck\n- trace persisted\n\nOtherwise use classical baseline or no trade.",
      "x": 1560,
      "y": 900,
      "width": 1530,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "blackboard",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Decision Blackboard\n\nSingle typed state per scan:\n- feature snapshot ids\n- local Gemma agent votes\n- neural prediction bundle\n- quantum optimizer result\n- existing DecisionPipeline candidates\n- portfolio state\n- risk precheck\n\nEvery downstream component reads this bundle.",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": -650,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "ensemble_fusion",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Ensemble Decision Engine\n\nCombines:\n- rule strategies\n- neural forecasts\n- local Gemma council votes\n- quantum allocation proposal\n- market regime\n- portfolio state\n\nMethods:\n- weighted voting by regime\n- uncertainty penalty\n- no-trade threshold\n- champion/challenger policy routing",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": -270,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 350,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "goal_governor",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## 5 Crore Goal Governor\n\nTracks:\n- yearly target\n- run-rate\n- capital required estimate\n- max drawdown budget\n- strategy contribution\n- probability of target under Monte Carlo\n\nAllowed: increase research priority or reduce risk.\nNot allowed: automatically raise hard risk limits.",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": 140,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 360,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "risk_final",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Deterministic Final Risk Layer\n\nExisting controls stay final:\n- RiskEngine\n- ComplianceGuard\n- CapitalProtection\n- EventRiskGuard\n- ManualApprovalGate\n- LiveReadinessAggregator\n- kill switch\n- OMS duplicate guard\n- position reconciliation\n\nAny veto blocks the trade.",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": 560,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "order_router",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Order Construction and Execution\n\nApproved proposals become normal `OrderIntent` objects.\n\nExisting path preserved:\n`ExecutionScheduler -> InstrumentLockManager -> RateLimiter -> Broker -> FillProcessor -> ExitManager`.\n\nAttach trace id, policy id, model ids, quantum backend, agent vote summary, and risk decision.",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": 940,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "broker_controls",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Broker and Live Controls\n\nModes:\n- BACKTEST\n- SHADOW\n- PAPER\n- LIVE_CANARY\n- LIVE_APPROVED\n\nLive rules:\n- small capital canary first\n- manual promotion required\n- immediate rollback on stale data, rejection spike, drawdown, drift, or unexpected slippage",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": 1330,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 330,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "feedback_loop",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Learning Feedback Loop\n\nAfter every fill/rejection:\n- update PortfolioLedger\n- persist OMS event\n- compute slippage attribution\n- update strategy score\n- update meta-labels\n- update model performance\n- update optimizer realized score\n- create postmortem item when loss exceeds threshold",
      "x": 3410,
      "y": 1710,
      "width": 1420,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "walk_forward",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Purged Walk-Forward Lab\n\nValidation:\n- purged train/test split\n- embargo around label horizon\n- rolling retrain windows\n- out-of-sample metrics\n- transaction costs and slippage\n- regime-specific performance\n\nRequired before model/policy promotion.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "monte_carlo",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Monte Carlo and Stress Desk\n\nRuns:\n- return-path reshuffling\n- volatility shock\n- spread widening\n- fill latency\n- gap risk\n- correlation breakdown\n- losing-streak simulation\n\nOutputs target-achievement and drawdown probability.",
      "x": -3160,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "strategy_tournament",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Strategy Tournament\n\nChampion/challenger process:\n- baseline strategy\n- neural-enhanced variant\n- LLM-reasoned variant\n- quantum-allocated variant\n- RL-trained variant\n\nPromotion only after costs and risk.",
      "x": -2180,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 860,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_shadow",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Shadow and Paper Trading\n\nBefore live:\n1. replay backtest\n2. shadow live signals\n3. paper trading with slippage\n4. live canary with small cap\n5. live approval after review\n\nAll modes share trace schema.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 2790,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "policy_promotion",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Policy Promotion Gate\n\nRequires:\n- tests pass\n- data quality pass\n- OOS profit factor threshold\n- Sharpe/Sortino threshold\n- max drawdown threshold\n- slippage sensitivity pass\n- paper/live canary pass\n- manual approval\n\nRollback pointer mandatory.",
      "x": -3160,
      "y": 2790,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "postmortem_factory",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Automated Postmortems\n\nFor every large loss or unexpected rejection:\n- pull trace\n- compare prediction vs realized path\n- classify failure mode\n- create research issue\n- mark decay if repeated\n\nLLM summarizes; code computes metrics.",
      "x": -2180,
      "y": 2790,
      "width": 860,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "ray_cluster",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Compute Fabric\n\nLocal phase:\n- existing FastAPI app\n- local workers\n- optional GPU workstation\n\nScale phase:\n- Ray cluster for distributed training/backtests\n- Ray Train/Tune\n- Ray RLlib\n- Ray Serve/vLLM",
      "x": -940,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 340,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "model_registry_node",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Model Registry and Experiment Tracking\n\nTrack:\n- model weights\n- training data range\n- feature schema\n- metrics\n- risk limits used\n- promotion state\n- rollback version\n\nSuggested: MLflow-style registry plus existing `models/` bootstrap.",
      "x": -110,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 310,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "observability",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Observability\n\nMetrics:\n- latency per layer\n- local model inference time\n- optimizer runtime\n- order queue depth\n- fill quality\n- drawdown\n- target progress\n\nSuggested: OpenTelemetry + Prometheus + Grafana.",
      "x": 700,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 310,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "secrets_security",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Security and Isolation\n\nRules:\n- broker credentials only in execution service\n- LLM agents have no broker tools\n- provider tokens isolated\n- signed policy versions\n- append-only audit log\n- manual approval for live policy changes\n- no secrets in traces/prompts",
      "x": -940,
      "y": 2800,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "command_center",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Command Center Dashboard\n\nAdd views:\n- AI Council\n- Neural Lab\n- Quantum Lab\n- Strategy Tournament\n- Goal Governor\n- Policy Promotion\n- Trace Replay\n- Risk Console\n\nReact/Zustand/WebSocket remains.",
      "x": 1810,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_view",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## AI Council View\n\nShows:\n- each agent vote\n- local model used\n- retrieved evidence\n- confidence\n- disagreement\n- supervisor decision\n- trace id\n\nExplains why a trade was blocked or proposed.",
      "x": 2800,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "quantum_view",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Quantum Lab View\n\nShows:\n- candidate basket\n- QUBO/CQM objective\n- constraints\n- classical baseline\n- Qiskit/D-Wave status\n- selected basket\n- stability tests\n- realized performance vs baseline",
      "x": 3790,
      "y": 2410,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "goal_view",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Goal and Risk View\n\nShows:\n- yearly target progress\n- required run-rate\n- probability of target\n- drawdown budget remaining\n- exposure heatmap\n- stop-trading reasons\n- target-pressure warnings",
      "x": 1810,
      "y": 2790,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 290,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase1",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 1 - Data and Trace Foundation\n\n- trace ids across scan/order lifecycle\n- durable decision trace store\n- feature schema versioning\n- label/outcome factory\n- model registry skeleton\n- no behavior change to live trading",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 250,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase2",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 2 - Local Gemma Agent Council\n\n- build deterministic supervisor\n- add Gemma-compatible model gateway\n- support vLLM/Ollama/llama.cpp local runtimes\n- implement news, quant, risk critic, PM, execution agents\n- enforce structured JSON and no broker tools\n- add AI Council dashboard",
      "x": -2620,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase3",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 3 - Neural Lab\n\n- tensor feature pipeline\n- forecasting ensemble\n- volatility/tail-risk model\n- GNN correlation model\n- calibrated uncertainty\n- advisory until validated",
      "x": -1100,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 250,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase4",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 4 - Quantum Lab\n\n- QUBO/CQM builder\n- classical baseline optimizer\n- optional Qiskit backend\n- optional D-Wave backend\n- quantum kernel shadow classifier\n- Quantum Lab dashboard",
      "x": 420,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 250,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase5",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 5 - Multi-Agent RL Simulator\n\n- FinRL/RLlib-style environment\n- train entry/exit/sizing/hedge/execution policies\n- adversarial slippage simulations\n- compare to rule and neural baselines\n- shadow only at first",
      "x": 1940,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 250,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "phase6",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Phase 6 - Promotion and Canary\n\n- strategy tournament\n- paper trading\n- live canary caps\n- rollback automation\n- target probability dashboard\n- strict manual approval before larger capital",
      "x": 3460,
      "y": 3910,
      "width": 1380,
      "height": 250,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "prompt_pointer",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Implementation Prompt\n\nUse companion file:\n`CLAUDE_QUANTUM_MULTI_AGENT_PROMPT.md`\n\nIt implements this architecture with Phase 2 as local Gemma-compatible model gateway, not custom model creation.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 4310,
      "width": 3000,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "ref_summary",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Reference Summary\n\nGemma 4: local/open model family used as the agent brain through a local gateway.\n\nOpenAI Agents and Microsoft Agent Framework: manager agents, handoffs, structured outputs, parallel specialist agents, and guardrails.\n\nRay RLlib and FinRL: scalable reinforcement learning and finance simulation patterns.\n\nIBM/Qiskit and D-Wave: quantum/classical hybrid optimization suitable for constrained portfolio selection experiments.",
      "x": -4140,
      "y": 5400,
      "width": 4400,
      "height": 340,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "ref_links",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Source URLs\n\nGemma 4 official: https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/technology/developers-tools/gemma-4/\nOpenAI multi-agent orchestration: https://openai.github.io/openai-agents-python/multi_agent/\nMicrosoft Agent Framework orchestration: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/agent-framework/workflows/orchestrations/\nRay RLlib: https://docs.ray.io/en/master/rllib/index.html\nFinRL-Meta overview: https://finrl.readthedocs.io/en/latest/finrl_meta/overview.html\nPyTorch Forecasting TFT: https://pytorch-forecasting.readthedocs.io/en/v0.5.1/api/pytorch_forecasting.models.temporal_fusion_transformer.TemporalFusionTransformer.html\nIBM Quantum Portfolio Optimizer: https://quantum.cloud.ibm.com/docs/en/guides/global-data-quantum-optimizer\nD-Wave hybrid solvers: https://docs.dwavequantum.com/en/latest/industrial_optimization/leap_hybrid.html\nQiskit quantum kernels: https://qiskit-community.github.io/qiskit-machine-learning/apidocs/qiskit_machine_learning.kernels.html",
      "x": 440,
      "y": 5400,
      "width": 4300,
      "height": 420,
      "color": "5"
    }
  ],
